rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all ice hockey coaches. Hockey coaches direct the hockey team during games and practices, prepares the team's strategy, and decides which players will participate in games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hockey Coach
current_team
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:sports.sports_team_coach.teams_coached instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.sports_team_coach.teams_coached ]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of ice hockey leagues. In the NHL, there are two conferences: Eastern and Western. In the NCAA, college-level hockey, there are several conferences dividing the divisions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hockey Conference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an ice hockey league to another ice hockey league that is part of it, e.g. a division to a conference.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: League

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an ice hockey conference to a team that is part of the conference.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Teams

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of ice hockey divisions. In the NFL, divisions sub-divide the two conferences. In the NCAA, for college-level hockey, divisions are the top-level sub-divisions of the organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hockey Division

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data for a goaltender in hockey's season statistics. For all other positions, please use mso:ice_hockey.player_season_statistics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Goaltender Season Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the number of goals scored while the goaltender was off the ice.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Empty Net Goals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the number of games the goaltender played for the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games Played

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the number of games in which the goaltender started, but did not play the entire game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games Started

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the number of goals scored against the goaltender.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Goals Against

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the goals against average for the goaltender for the given season. Goals against average are the mean goals-per-60 minutes scored on the goaltender.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Goals Against Average

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the overtime losses attibuted to the goaltender for the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Overtime Losses

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the mso:ice_hockey.player earning the statistics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the number of shots on goals the goaltender has saved for the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Saves

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the mso:sports.season for which the statistics hold.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the number of shots on goal the goaltender has faced for the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shots on Goal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the number of shutouts for the goaltender for the given season. Shutouts are games in which the goaltender had no goals scored against them and was the only goaltender for the team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shutouts

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the total number of minutes the goaltender was on the ice for the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Minutes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all ice hockey players. Players on skates work in teams to move the puck across the ice and shoot it into the opponent's net.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hockey Player
former_team_s
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:sports.pro_athlete.team instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.pro_athlete.team]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an ice hockey player to a position held by the hockey player, e.g. goaltender or winger.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hockey Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an ice hockey player to a descriptor indicating whether the hockey player is left-handed, right-handed, ambidextrous, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shoot

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data for the statistics of a given ice_hockey.player, except goaltenders, during a given season. For the statistics specific to a goaltender, see mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player Season Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the number of assists attributed to the player for the given season. Assists are those actions by one player that aids another player in scoring a goal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Assists

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.player_season_statistics to the number of game-tying goals attributed to the player for the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Game-tying Goals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.player_season_statistics to the number of game winning goals attributed to the player for the given season. A goal is considered game winning when the team would win the game without scoring any more goals, for example, the third goal in a 5???2 win.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Game-winning Goals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the number of games the given player played during the hockey season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games Played

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the number of goals attributed to the player for the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Goals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.player_season_statistics to the number of penalties, in minutes, attributed to the player for the given season. It represents the total assessed length of penalties the player has accrued.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Penalty in Minutes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.player_season_statistics to the mso:ice_hockey.player to which the statistics are attributed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.goaltender_season_statistics to the player's goal differential for the given season. The differential is increased for those players on the ice for the team scoring the goal; the plus???minus statistic is decreased by one for those players on the ice for the team allowing the goal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Plus-minus

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.player_season_statistics to the number of power play goals attributed to the player for the given season. Power plays occur when one of the teams have at least one player serving a penalty, and the opposing team gains a numerical advantage on the ice.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Power Play Goals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.player_season_statistics to the mso:sports.season for which the statistics hold.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.player_season_statistics to the number of short-handed goals attributed to the player for the given season. The short-handed goal is scored when a team's on-ice players are outnumbered by the opposing team's.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Short-handed Goals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:ice_hockey.player_season_statistics to the number of shots on goal attributed to the player for the given season. For non-goaltender players, this statistic measures the number of times the player attempted to make a goal that would have scored, had the goaltender not saved it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shots on Goal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all hockey positions. These are the general roles the players of ice hockey take in the playing of a game. Included in this type are goaltender, centre, and defencemen.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hockey Position
